Vulnerability.Title: Insertion of Sensitive Information Into Sent Data Vulnerability in csfd daemon

cvrf:Acknowledgment.cvrf:Description: Internally discovered and reported by Gwendal Guégniaud of Fortinet Product Security team.

cvrf:Note.#text: An Insertion of Sensitive Information Into Sent Data Vulnerability in Fortimanager, FortiMail, FortiNDR, FortOS, FortiPAM, FortiProxy, FortiRecorder, FortiTester, FortiVoice, FortiWeb csfd daemon may allow a remote authenticated attacker to read small and non-arbitrary parts of memory.
